cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper focuses on the front-end text processing module for Mandarin TTS, which involves natural language processing and linguistic feature extraction. 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper is ultimately concerned with synthesizing speech, which falls under the domain of sound. 
- cs.SI (Speech and Audio Processing): The paper deals with speech synthesis, which is a subfield of speech and audio processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The proposed unified front-end model is based on sequence-to-sequence learning, which is a popular machine learning technique. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses neural network models (Tacotron and WaveRNN) for speech synthesis, which falls under the domain of neural computing.
